                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word God is not rubricated in the first three works; the word Mary is rubricated in the final two works</desc>
                  <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#112v #113r" facs="115 115">folss. 112v, 113r, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#121r #121v" facs="123 124">121r, 121v</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1086StrikingHead">The Striking of the Head, ኵርዓተ፡ ርእሱ፡</ref></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iir(etco)" facs="002">Fol. iir(etco)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4306GabraMa">Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</persName></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> attended by the angels <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4377Gabriel">Gabriel</persName></desc></decoNote>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#1r #23r #33r #45v #64r #72r #77v #89r #99r #102r #107r #107v #124v" facs="003 025 035 048 066 074 080 091 101 104 109 110 127">folss. 1r, 23r, 33r, 45v, 64r, 72r, 77v, 89r, 99r, 102r, 107r, 107v, 124v, </locus> (haräg);
                  <locus target="#7v #132v #139r" facs="010 135 141">7v, 132v, 139r, </locus> (multiple full stops);
                  <locus target="#15r #140v" facs="017 143">15r, 140v, </locus> (multiple full stops and a line of alternating red and black dots);
                  <locus target="#53v" facs="056">53v</locus> (line of red and black dots)
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#145v #146r" facs="148">Fols. 145v, 146r</locus>
                    <desc type="GuestText">
                    <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3308Nicene">Nicene Creed</title>
                    Incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">እዜምር: ለከ: ጸሎተ: ሃይማኖት: ነዓምን: በ፩ አምላክ: እግዚአብሔር: አብ: አሃዜ ኵሉ: ዓለም: ገባሬ: ሰማያት: ወምድር:<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #146v" facs="001 149">Fols. ir(ecto), 146v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Pentrials and scrawls
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#59r" facs="061">Fol. 59r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    A small, red cross with the words “Half of it” is written in the margin to mark the midpoint of the <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</ref>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#77r" facs="079">Fol. 77r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    blank
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#3r #10r #16v #17v #30r" facs="005 012 019 020 032">Fols. 3r, 10r, 16v, 17v, 30r</locus>
                    <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#9v #37v #63v #83r" facs="012 040 066 085">Fols. 9v, 37v, 63v, 83r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    lines of text are written interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                    lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (: :) marking the location where the text is to be inserted, <locus target="#71r" facs="073"> f. 71r, line 8</locus>,
                    and in another case where the symbol (+) is used, <locus target="#104v" facs="107"> f. 104v, line 2</locus>;
                    erasure markings are visible, <locus target="#3v #43v #54r" facs="006 046 056">3v, 43v, 54r</locus>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#70v #71v" facs="073 074">Fols. 70v, 71v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#44r #45r" facs="046 047">Fols. 44r, 45r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    The scribe’s chosen aspect ratio for the codex combined with the script size forces the scribe to complete the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout). But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line throughout the codex
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
